frameDefinitions: In this frame an Agent continues to possess a Theme for a Duration of time. '' 'In her heart she must retain bitterness against those who had killed him.'
Water in some solid or liquid form (the Precipitation) falls from the sky at a particular Place and Time, lasting for a particular Duration.
An Agent has placed a Theme in an accessible but somewhat out of the way Location for the purposes of maintaining it free from harm and illegitimate use while it is not being used.
A Material has been processed (generally industrially) to some Degree in order to make it more useful for some (usually implicit) function.
A Recipient (who may or may not be agentive) ends up in possession of a Mass_theme (which may be conceptualized as a single mass entity, or may be a group of individual entities).
A Supply of a Resource is kept safe and available for a future Use.
frameExamples: In her heart she must <t>retain</t> bitterness against those who had killed him.
Bogs <t>accumulate</t> carbon for thousands of years.
Our <t>supply</t> of food is running low.
listRoleDefinitions: The person who has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity which the <fen>Agent</fen> possesses for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The water in liquid or solid form that falls from the sky is the Precipitation. This role is incorporated in many LUs in this frame.
The area which experiences precipitation.
When the event occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who has placed the <fen>Theme</fen> in the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that is kept in a <fen>Location</fen> by the <fen>Agent</fen>
The location where the <fen>Theme</fen> is kept. Some, though not all, LUs in this frame incorporate this FE.
<fen>Time</fen> is the time period during which the <fen>Theme</fen> is stored.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the Storing occurs.
The substance which is altered in some useful way.
The <fen>Recipient</fen> indicates the entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Mass_theme</fen>.
The collection of objects that ends up in the <fen>Recipient</fen>'s possession.
When the event occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> denotes where the <fen>Mass_theme</fen> is acquired.
This role denotes the <fen>Supply</fen> of <fen>Resource</fen>s. It is incorporated into each LU in this frame.
The goods or commodity that is being stored in a <fen>Supply</fen>.
The future <fen>Use</fen> for the <fen>Resource</fen>.
The entity that possesses the <fen>Supply</fen>.
listRoleExamples: At all times <fex>the Saxon government</fex> held on to its insistently practiced political tradition.
Once you've got a War Bond, hang on to <fex>it</fex> for the full ten years of its life.
Margerite held on to the key <fex>on Wednesday</fex> until I returned to pick it up.
He will retain <fex>in his heart</fex> the memory of the vast Holocaust.
It will probably be raining <fex>at five o'clock</fex>.
India has made great strides in agriculture and now not only meets it own grain needs but has a sizeable reserve <fex>of basic grains, mainly rice and wheat</fex>.
Due to restrictions imposed by our export control, the Japanese have begun to use a portion of their <fex>war</fex> reserve of petroleum.
In 1997, <fex>France's</fex> stock of unirradiated civil plutonium increased to 72 tons.
